# <%= @module_name %>

An ADK-powered agent built with [ADK Elixir](https://github.com/zeroasterisk/adk-elixir). 🏴‍☠️

## Getting Started

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
mix deps.get
```

### 2. Set your API key

```bash
export GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
```

Get a key at [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey).

### 3. Run the agent

```bash
iex -S mix
```

```elixir
<%= @module_name %>.Agent.run("Greet me as Captain Hook!")
# => "Ahoy, Captain Hook! Welcome aboard, ye scurvy dog! 🏴‍☠️"

<%= @module_name %>.Agent.run("What is 42 * 13?")
# => "The answer be 546.0, matey!"
```
<%= if @phoenix do %>
### 4. Start the web server

```elixir
<%= @module_name %>.Router.start(port: 8080)
```

This exposes the ADK Web API at `http://localhost:8080`, compatible with the
[adk-web](https://github.com/google/adk-web) React frontend.

**Endpoints:**

- `GET /health` — Health check
- `GET /list-apps` — List agents
- `POST /run` — Run agent synchronously
- `POST /run_sse` — Run agent with SSE streaming
<% end %>
### Run tests

Tests use a mock LLM backend — no API key needed:

```bash
mix test
```

## Project Structure

```
<%= @app_name %>/
├── lib/
│   ├── <%= @app_name %>.ex              # Main module
│   ├── <%= @app_name %>/
│   │   ├── agent.ex           # Agent definition
│   │   ├── tools.ex           # Tool definitions<%= if @phoenix do %>
│   │   ├── router.ex          # Web endpoints<% end %>
│   │   └── application.ex     # OTP Application
├── config/
│   ├── config.exs             # Base config (model: <%= @model %>)
│   ├── dev.exs                # Dev config
│   └── test.exs               # Test config (mock LLM)
└── test/
    └── <%= @app_name %>/
        └── agent_test.exs     # Agent tests
```

## Configuration

The default model is `<%= @model %>`. Change it in `config/config.exs`:

```elixir
config :<%= @app_name %>,
  model: "gemini-2.5-pro"
```

